    "text": " 37 AM / Updated 25 minutes ago Trade unions at Volkswagen's Skoda Auto reject wage offer, prepare strike Reuters Staff 1 Min Read PRAGUE (Reuters) - Trade unions at Volkswagen’s Skoda Auto plants in Czech Republic have rejected a wage offer from the carmaker and started preparations for a possible time-unlimited strike, the unions said on Thursday. Skoda Auto’s board will discuss the situation on Feb. 19, the unions said in a statement on their website. Reporting by Robert Muller; Editing by Adrian Croft",
